params.fees_: Array of pool fees associated with each token pair in the path
params.tokens_: Array of token addresses defining the swap path

params.asset_: Address of the asset to be deployed
params.assetsAmount_: Amount of assets to be deployed
params.receiver_: Address of the asset receiver (this contract)

returns._0: liquidToken Address of the liquid token received after deployment
returns._1: liquidTokenAmount Amount of liquid tokens received after deployment

getRoleAdmin(bytes32).details: Returns the admin role that controls `role`. See {grantRole} and {revokeRole}. To change a role's admin, use {_setRoleAdmin}.

params.source_: Specifies from where to get the price when no oracle is defined
params.token_: Address of the token to retrieve the price for

returns._0: The price of the token in ETH

grantRole(bytes32,address).details: Grants `role` to `account`. If `account` had not been already granted `role`, emits a {RoleGranted} event. Requirements: - the caller must have ``role``'s admin role. May emit a {RoleGranted} event.

params.vaultAddress_: Address of the vault associated with this strategy

paused().details: Returns true if the contract is paused, and false otherwise.

renounceRole(bytes32,address).details: Revokes `role` from the calling account. Roles are often managed via {grantRole} and {revokeRole}: this function's purpose is to provide a mechanism for accounts to lose their privileges if they are compromised (such as when a trusted device is misplaced). If the calling account had been revoked `role`, emits a {RoleRevoked} event. Requirements: - the caller must be `callerConfirmation`. May emit a {RoleRevoked} event.

revokeRole(bytes32,address).details: Revokes `role` from `account`. If `account` had been granted `role`, emits a {RoleRevoked} event. Requirements: - the caller must have ``role``'s admin role. May emit a {RoleRevoked} event.

params.adaptersDeployPath_: Array of new adapter addresses for deployment

params.adaptersWithdrawPath_: Array of new adapter addresses for withdrawal

params.withdrawStrategyAddress_: New address for the withdrawal strategy

params.source_: Specifies from where to get the price when no oracle is defined

returns._0: deployedAssetsValue The new valuation of the deployed assets

DEPLOYMENT_ADAPTERS_QTY().notice: Number of deployment adapters specified for this strategy

REVERT_MSG().notice: Revert message used to indicate that a function is not allowed/implemented

VAULT_MANAGER_ROLE().notice: Role identifier for managing vault operations

WITHDRAW_ADAPTERS_QTY().notice: Number of withdrawal adapters specified for this strategy

adaptersDeployPath(uint256).notice: Path of adapters used for deploying assets

adaptersWithdrawPath(uint256).notice: Path of adapters used for withdrawing assets

buildPath(address[],uint24[]).notice: Configures the path for token swaps on Uniswap V3

deployedAssetsValue().notice: Total value of assets currently deployed by this strategy

executeDeploymentStrategy(address,addres.notice: Executes the deployment strategy for the given assets

executeHarvest().notice: This function is not applicable in this strategy and will always revert

getDeployedAssetsValue().notice: Retrieves the current value of assets deployed by the strategy

getFirstDepositAdapter().notice: Retrieves the address of the adapter used for asset deployment

getTokenPrice(address,uint8).notice: Retrieves the price of a token using the withdrawal adapter

initialize(address,address,address[],add.notice: Initializes the strategy with addresses and paths

liquidTokenAddress().notice: Address of the liquid token used in the strategy

pause().notice: Pauses the contract (only callable by admin)

priceFeedPerToken(address).notice: Addresses of the priceFeed per token

setAdaptersDeployPath(address[]).notice: Replaces the entire deployment path for adapters with new addresses

setAdaptersWithdrawPath(address[]).notice: Replaces the entire withdrawal path for adapters with new addresses

setLiquidTokenAddress(address).notice: Sets a new liquid token address for the strategy

setPriceFeedPerToken(address,address).notice: Set the feed address to get price for a specific token

setWithdrawStrategyAddress(address).notice: Sets the address for the withdrawal strategy

setWrappedLiquidTokenAddress(address).notice: Sets a new address for the wrapper of liquid token

swapPath().notice: Encoded swap path and fee information used by Uniswap V3

unpause().notice: Unpauses the contract (only callable by admin)

updateDeployedAssetVaule(uint8).notice: Updates the valuation of deployed assets based on current prices

vaultAddress().notice: Main vault address associated with this strategy

withdrawStrategyAddress().notice: Address of the strategy for withdrawals

wrappedLiquidTokenAddress().notice: Address of the wrapper for the liquidToken
